summary:
A Doctor with 11 years of experience in different medical fields such as Emergency Medicine, General Surgery, Intensive Care, eFAST/POCUS US protocols, EMS and Sport`s Medicine, certified by American Heart Association as BLS, ACLS and PALS provider, certified by American College of Surgeons as Advanced Trauma Life Support provider and by International Trauma Life Support as an Advanced Provider. Actively registered with Ukrainian Medical Council.

I have got international work experience with my previous employment at MSC Mediterranean Shipping Company and Ambassador Cruise Line. Besides, I have experience of working along with the Italian Red Cross, and at the time of the Ukrainian crisis I volunteered as a Medical Doctor for Ukrainian refugees in Romania. Currently I am employed by Royal Caribbean Group as an Onboard Doctor.

I am passionate about improving the health and well-being of people around the world, and I constantly update my professional knowledge and skills. 

Please feel free to reach out to me if you have any questions.

message.text:
Sincerely honoured to be an official graduate of “GUSI Essentials Course” organized by Global Ultrasound Institute (GUSI)!

Tremendous thanks to organizers and all physicians involved, who have dedicated much of their time to make this course so interesting and captivating!😍

PS: my high recommendation to all physicians who have passion to master the bedside ultrasound technique👌
